material.mattext: Match the following quantities with their standard SI units.
A burn on your arm from 100 °C steam is more severe than a burn from 100 °C water because...
100 °C steam contains more energy than 100 °C water.
steam is a gas, which has spread-out molecules.
H2O molecules in the form of steam have more degrees of freedom than H2O molecules in the form of liquid water.

A `m` kilogram glass bowl has a temperature of `TF` °F when placed in a freezer.  How much heat, in kcal, will the freezer have to remove from the bowl to cool it to 12 °F?

 

Heat capacity of the bowl, c = `c` kcal / (kg °C)
Why does a piece of metal feel cooler to the touch than a piece of wood at the same temperatures?
You sense heat flowing from your body as cool, and metal is a better conductor than wood.
Metals lose heat rapidly and becomes cooler than wood.
Wood is always at a higher temperature than metals because it is an insulator.
Wood holds more heat because of air in the spaces where cells once existed.
A heat engine is supplied with `QH` kcal of heat and dumps `QC` kcal of heat through the exhaust. What is the efficiency, as a percentage, of this engine?
